The Herald Joseph Madzimure – Senior Reporter FORMER Nigerian President Olusegun Obasanjo, who is also the chairman of the Johannesburg-based think tank Brenthurst Foundation, South Africa met with President Mnangagwa at State House today seeking to scout for investment opportunities in the country. <img class="wp-image-310729 size-large" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2017/07/5001-630x378.jpg" alt="" width="630" height="378" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2017/07/5001-630x378.jpg 630w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2017/07/5001-315x189.jpg 315w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2017/07/5001.jpg 750w" sizes="(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px" /> Mr Olusegun Obasanjo Speaking soon after the meeting with the President,  Mr Obasanjo said they are in the country to seek investment opportunities. <img class="wp-image-460722 size-full" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/11/Greg-Barrington.jpg" alt="" width="573" height="700" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/11/Greg-Barrington.jpg 573w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/11/Greg-Barrington-295x360.jpg 295w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/11/Greg-Barrington-557x680.jpg 557w" sizes="(max-width: 573px) 100vw, 573px" /> Dr Gregory John Barrington Mills (pic from uj.ac.za) “I have along with me some people who have interests in investing here in Zimbabwe, that is what we have come here for. “We cannot talk of development without investment, domestic investment, foreign investment and regional investment. The meeting went on very well,” said Mr Obasanjo. 